Treat a newline-free string that the operating system cannot use as a file path (for example, one containing an embedded null byte or one that is too long) as calendar data rather than letting an :exc:`OSError` propagate from :meth:`Component.from_ical <icalendar.cal.component.Component.from_ical>`. Such input now raises a consistent :exc:`ValueError` across platforms, and the str-vs-path boundary is covered by tests. @uwezkhan
